This paper is primarily focused on the Network Function Virtualization (NFV) paradigm, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper discusses the optimization of resource utilization while improving the reliability of Service Function Chains (SFCs), which involves the use of Linear Programming (LP) models and active-active configurations. This suggests that the paper could also fall under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of replications and migrations on SFC reliability, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses load balancing, which could fall under the sub-category of programming languages (cs.PL).
